This paper is about dialogue management in conversational artificial intelligence, which falls under the category of natural language processing (NLP) and machine learning. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers NLP and related topics. The paper also discusses the use of neural networks, which suggests that cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence) and cs.LG (Machine Learning) are also likely sub-categories. Additionally, the paper involves experimentation and evaluation of the proposed model, which could fall under cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing) or cs.SD (Software Engineering).
